# **THE EMOTIONAL REP**

This work isn’t cold mechanics. Under the surface of every avoided task is a swamp of emotion: fear of failure, fear of success, shame of starting late, the exquisite pain of maybe not being perfect.

When you do the 2-Minute Drill, you’re not just opening a document. You’re walking into that swamp. You’re saying to the fear, “You’re big, you’re scary, but I can stand in you for 120 seconds.” And when the timer beeps, you walk out. You prove you can enter and exit the emotion. It doesn’t own you.

The Decision Sprint isn’t about chairs and VR headsets. It’s about practicing the audacity of choice. It’s rehab for atrophied agency. Every “I will” is a tiny rebellion against the helplessness that procrastination breeds.

The Fuel Gauge Check is the ultimate act of self-kindness. It’s stopping the self-flagellation of “I’m so lazy” and replacing it with the curious, gentle question: “What’s really going on here?” You become your own coach, not your own critic.

